	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<pb facs="EHRI-DK-19430528_01.jpg" n="1"/>
				<p>The <term ref="#t642" type="subject">persecution</term> of <term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jews</term> in <placeName
						ref="#republic-of-bulgaria">Bulgaria</placeName></p>
				<p>The <term ref="#t1007" type="subject">legation</term> has the honour of dispatching to the <orgName ref="#g006627">Royal
						Ministry</orgName> a report received from the Consulate of <placeName ref="#sofia">Sofia</placeName>, No. 56. of <date
						when="1943-05-28"> 28 May 1943</date>, on the above-quoted topic.</p>
				<pb facs="EHRI-DK-19430528_02.jpg" n="2"/>
				<p>With reference to previous reports, the Consulate hereby has the honour to report that according to a regulation of the <orgName
						ref="#g007263">Minister of the Interior</orgName>, published in the current <term ref="#t1068" type="subject">Press</term> on
					the 25th of this month, all <term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jews</term> in <placeName ref="#sofia">Sofia</placeName> must be
						<term ref="#t1173" type="subject">moved</term> to the Province. As written in the Consulate's Report no. 94 from <date
						when="1942-09-01"> 1.9.1942</date> all unemployed <term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jews</term> were to <term ref="#t625"
						type="subject">leave</term>
					<placeName ref="#sofia">Sofia</placeName>. However, since only a few <term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jews</term> have left
						<placeName ref="#sofia">Sofia</placeName>, the <term ref="#t595" type="subject">Commission on Jewish Affairs</term> is now
					carrying out an expulsion. Every <term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jewish</term>
					<term ref="#t819" type="subject">family</term> in Sofia is given a 3-day time limit to leave <placeName ref="#sofia"
						>Sofia</placeName>, during which the provincial town is announced to which they have to relocate. Those <term ref="#t864"
						type="subject">Jews</term> who do not comply with this regulation will be <term ref="#t880" type="subject">expelled</term>
					from the country immediately.</p>
				<p>About 23,000 <term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jews</term> are affected by this Regulation. In <placeName ref="#sofia"
						>Sofia</placeName>, there are approx. 25,000 <term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jews</term>, and only <term ref="#t864"
						type="subject">Jews</term> who are <term ref="#t1149" type="subject">foreign</term> nationals, and <term ref="#t864"
						type="subject">Jews</term> who are <term ref="#t488" type="subject">civilized mobilized</term> can still remain in <placeName
						ref="#sofia">Sofia</placeName>. In old <placeName ref="#republic-of-bulgaria">Bulgaria</placeName>, there are approx. 41,000
						<term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jews</term>, including 18,000 in the Province. About 10,000 <term ref="#t864" type="subject"
						>Jews</term> are mobilized, and the majority are <term ref="#t489" type="subject">employed</term> by <term ref="#t556"
						type="subject">road construction workers</term>.</p>
				<p><persName ref="#ehri_dr_biering_erik_andreas_mathias">Erik Andreas Mathias Biering</persName></p>
